  <text>
    <front>
      <div type="printedheader">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7795_p1">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l1"/>
          <fw>THE PATENT
        <lb xml:id="p1-l2"/>TUNNELING
        <lb xml:id="p1-l3"/>&amp; MINING MACHINE
        <lb xml:id="p1-l4"/>COMPANY.
        <lb xml:id="p1-l5"/>LIMITED</fw>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="dateline">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_7795_p2">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l6"/>
          <fw>18. Finsbury Circus,
            <lb xml:id="p1-l7"/>
                        <placeName type="place" key="London (UK)">London</placeName>. <choice>
                            <abbr>E. C.</abbr>
                            <expan>Eastern Central (östlicher Stadtteil)</expan>
                        </choice> </fw>
          <date when="1872-05-16">
           16<hi rend="sup">th</hi> May <fw>187</fw>2</date>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div type="address">
        <p rend="center" xml:id="K_7795_p3">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l8"/>From <choice>
                        <abbr>Lt. Colonel</abbr>
                        <expan>Lieutenant Colonel (Oberstleutnant)</expan>
                    </choice> Holland
        <lb xml:id="p1-l9"/>President
        <lb xml:id="p1-l10"/>of the Patent Tunneling Mining Machine <choice>
                        <abbr>Co.</abbr>
                        <expan>Compagnia / Compagnie / Company (Gesellschaft)</expan>
                    </choice> Limited.
        <lb xml:id="p1-l11"/>To
        <lb xml:id="p1-l12"/>The President of the <choice>
                        <abbr>S<hi rend="sup">t</hi> </abbr>
                        <expan>Sankt / Sanct / Saint (heilig)</expan>
                    </choice> Gothard Railway Company
        <lb xml:id="p1-l13"/>
                    <choice>
                        <abbr>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> </abbr>
                        <expan>Doktor / Doctor</expan>
                    </choice> A. Escher
        <lb xml:id="p1-l14"/>Direction <choice>
                        <abbr>S<hi rend="sup">t</hi> </abbr>
                        <expan>Sankt / Sanct / Saint (heilig)</expan>
                    </choice> Gothard
        <lb xml:id="p1-l15"/>Bellevue
        <lb xml:id="p1-l16"/>
                    <placeName type="place" key="Luzern (Stadt)">Lucerne</placeName> <lb xml:id="p1-l17"/>Suisse.</p>
      </div>
      <div type="opener">
        <p rend="left" xml:id="K_7795_p4">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l18"/>Sir</p>
      </div>
    </front>
    <body>
            <div>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_7795_p5">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l19"/>I <date when="1872-05-15">yesterday</date> had the honour to send you a
        <lb xml:id="p1-l20"/>Tender made by this Company for boring the Great <placeName type="place" key="St. Gotthard (Pass)">S<hi rend="sup">t</hi> Gothard</placeName> <lb xml:id="p1-l21"/>Tunnel at rates which will complete the excavation of the
        <lb xml:id="p1-l22"/>whole Tunnel, 14,800 metres in lenght, 6 metres in height,
            <lb xml:id="p1-l23"/>and 8 metres in width in periods varying from 8½ years
            <lb xml:id="p1-l24"/>to 3½ years on certain terms per metre. 
        </p>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_7795_p6">
                    <lb xml:id="p1-l25"/>I now enclose for the information of your
        <lb xml:id="p1-l26"/>Engineer-in-Chief a photopraph of the Cutter-head and 
        <lb xml:id="p1-l27"/>Ram of the Machine which cut the 2.68 metres per hour <pb n="2"/>
                    <lb xml:id="p2-l1"/>reported by the <placeName type="place" key="Frankreich">French</placeName> Government Commission in 1868,
        <lb xml:id="p2-l2"/>Copy of which Report was forwarded to you <date when="1872-05-15">yesterday</date> <lb xml:id="p2-l3"/>with the Tender. I also forwarded by Book post
        <lb xml:id="p2-l4"/>
                    <date when="1872-05-15">yesterday</date> to your address the number of the «Mémoires
        <lb xml:id="p2-l5"/>et Compte-rendu des travaux de la Société des Ingénieurs
        <lb xml:id="p2-l6"/>Civil» from which the pamphlet attached to the Tender
        <lb xml:id="p2-l7"/>was extracted. 
        </p>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_7795_p7">
                    <lb xml:id="p2-l8"/>In an article by <choice>
                        <abbr>Mons.</abbr>
                        <expan>Monsieur (Herr)</expan>
                    </choice> <persName type="person" key="Flachat Eugène">Eugene Flachat</persName> on
        <lb xml:id="p2-l9"/>«La Suisse et les Communications Transalpine» published
        <lb xml:id="p2-l10"/>in the «Revue Moderne» in October 1868 mention is made
        <lb xml:id="p2-l11"/>of this Company's Machine and of its applicability to
        <lb xml:id="p2-l12"/>the <placeName type="place" key="St. Gotthard (Pass)">S<hi rend="sup">t</hi> Gothard</placeName> Tunnel, in preference to the small
            <lb xml:id="p2-l13"/>drilling Machines employed at the <placeName type="place" key="Mont-Cenis (Pass, F-I)">Mont Cenis</placeName>.
        </p>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_7795_p8">
                    <lb xml:id="p2-l14"/>
        <choice>
                        <abbr>Mons.</abbr>
                        <expan>Monsieur (Herr)</expan>
                    </choice>
        <persName type="person" key="Flachat Eugène">Flachat</persName> states that he saw the Machine 
        <lb xml:id="p2-l15"/>at work and mentions the rate at which it will
        <lb xml:id="p2-l16"/>cut through granite.
        </p>
      <p rend="indent" xml:id="K_7795_p9">
                    <lb xml:id="p2-l17"/>I shall feel very much obliged if you will be
        <lb xml:id="p2-l18"/>so kind as to acknowledge the receipt of this letter
        <lb xml:id="p2-l19"/>by return post if convenient for you to do so.
        </p>
      <p rend="right" xml:id="K_7795_p10">
                    <lb xml:id="p2-l20"/>I have the honour to be Sir
        <lb xml:id="p2-l21"/>your most obedient servant
        </p>
    </div>
        </body>
    <back>
      <div type="address">
        <p rend="right" xml:id="K_7795_p11">
                    <lb xml:id="p2-l22"/>Trev. J. Holland
        <lb xml:id="p2-l23"/>
        <choice>
                        <abbr>Lt. Colonel</abbr>
                        <expan>Lieutenant Colonel (Oberstleutnant)</expan>
                    </choice>
        <lb xml:id="p2-l24"/>President.</p> </div>
    </back>
